[1]The S.19 was a single-seat biplane flying boat with its engine mounted on struts above its hull and below its upper wing.
[2]The   Ansaldo San Giorgio 4E-29Aviation: SIAI racing seaplanes (Racing hydroplanes SIAI) engine drove a two-bladed pusher propeller.
[3]Small stabilizer floats were mounted beneath the lower wing on each side.
[4]Operational historyThe S.19s engine was not ready in time for the 1920 Schneider Trophy race, and the aircraft did not participate.
